verbose_text: Renal examination showed a renal failure with creatininemia at 37 mg/L and GFR of 17 mL/min/1.73 m 2 (MDRDS) associated with a proteinuria at 0.51 g/24 h. Complementary analysis showed total protein level of 55 g/L with high alkaline phosphate and uric acid levels of 497 UI/L and 86 mg/L, respectively, and LDH at 221 UI/L.
